OL,6,FMaking the emergency call, Mrs Mills
OL,7,Fsaid her husband had sustained a head
OL,8,Finjury in the attack, and claimed the
OL,9,Ftwo men - who were dressed all in
OL,10,Fblack with their faces covered - were
OL,11,Funknown to her, but one of them was
OL,12,FBerry, who she had been having an
OL,13,Faffair with for around three months.
OL,15,FThe other man was Steven Thomas, 47.
OL,16,FHe was found not guilty of conspiracy
OL,17,Fto murder by a jury, but admitted
OL,18,Fpossessing a firearm with intent to
OL,19,Fcause Mr Mills to believe that
OL,20,Funlawful violence would be used
OL,21,Fagainst him or another person.
